node.text: Photo by Michael Seeley @mseeley20 / At 3:14 a.m. ET on August 29, the CRS-23 mission launched from historic LC-39A at NASA's Kennedy Space Center, carrying 4,800 pounds (2,177 kilograms) of experiments, supplies, and hardware for the International Space Station. A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket lifted a cargo Dragon capsule to orbit bound for rendezvous with the ISS the next day. This was the view from the NASA Press Site about three miles (five kilometers) from the pad, seen in a 202-second exposure.

Photo by @irina_sigl_photography / This is the little Fatima Chapel on a cold winter day in Upper Bavaria. I liked the pure white of the fresh snow in contrast with the pattern of the clouds in the blue sky.
Nikon Z7, 24mm, f/11, 1/640s, ISO 200. #YourShotPhotographer #Bavaria

node.text:
Photo by @fdilekuyar / It rained continuously during my weeklong Black Sea trip, making it very difficult to shoot. The only good thing about the rain was the fog that suddenly started to descend to the plateaus when it stopped. Since the fog was moving quickly, I took a long-exposure photo with my 10-stop filter. The mist that looked like tulle became even more impressive. 
30-second exposure, f/9, ISO 100. #YourShotPhotographer

Photo by Jassen Todorov @jassensf / Each year between December and March, Northern California becomes the temporary home to thousands of migratory birds (geese, egrets, ducks, herons, and others). This aerial image was taken while I was flying my Piper Warrior plane. 
Nikon D810, 70-200mm, 1/500, f/2.8, ISO 125. #YourShotPhotographer #california #fromabove

node.text: Photo by Trần Tuấn Việt @vietsui / The K50 waterfall is also known as Hang Én because there is a large cave behind it that is home to thousands of swallows. The waterfall is 54 meters (177 feet) high and is located in the center of Kon Chư Răng Nature Reserve in Gia Lai Province, Vietnam. Follow @vietsui for more photos from Vietnam. #YourShotPhotographer #Nature #GiaLai #Vietnam

node.text:
Photo by @sarmistha_bera / Morning sunlight falls on a baby pineapple in this macro shot. I got a naturally dark surrounding since the light had not spread yet. When a pineapple plant is ready to produce a fruit, it sends up a flower stalk from the central point. In this stage, it looks gorgeous because of its vibrant colors, with red, purple, and green on the top. I grew a pineapple in my garden for the first time.
1/60, f/14, ISO 400. #YourShotPhotographer #macro #nature #photography

node.text: Photo by @karimiliya / Lava pours out of Iceland’s Fagradalsfjall volcano in this aerial view. New land is formed every second as molten rock pours from a fissure and covers the area. Many islands around the world are made through this violent process. This drone photo was created in compliance with local regulations. #YourShotPhotographer

node.text:
Photo by @doug_gimesy / Soon, but not yet / After being placed in a container for transport to a bush release site, a female koala tries to escape before the lid is closed and she starts the last leg of her journey back to the wild. She was rescued and successfully treated following the 2019-2020 Australian bushfires, when over 30 million acres burned. Some have estimated that 25 to 50 percent of the koala population burned to death, with many that survived suffering horrific injuries.
So, what can we all do now? Help tackle climate change and support those who work to make the planet a better place and help our wildlife. #YourShotPhotographer #koala #bushfire #koalacare
